.TH LINUX-HELLO 1 "18 December 2025" "linux-hello 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NOM
hello \- Linux facial authentication system with PAM integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hello
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hello
is a facial authentication system for Linux that integrates with PAM for secure
login and system access. It uses InsightFace deep learning model for face recognition
and supports multiple languages.
.SH COMMANDES
.TP
.B add USER
Register a new user face. The system will capture the face image from the camera
and store the facial embedding.
.TP
.B test USER
Test authentication for a specific user. The system will attempt to recognize
the user's face from the camera.
.TP
.B list
List all registered users with their enrollment status.
.TP
.B remove USER
Unregister a user and delete their stored facial data.
.TP
.B doctor
Run system diagnostics to verify installation integrity. Checks:
.RS
.IP \- 2
Virtual environment presence
.IP \-
Python installation
.IP \-
InsightFace importability
.IP \-
Daemon service status
.IP \-
Unix socket connectivity
.IP \-
Camera accessibility
.IP \-
Registered faces database
.RE
.TP
.B select-camera
Interactive camera selection tool. Lists available cameras and allows
configuration of the default camera for authentication.
.TP
.B enroll USER
Alias for
.B add USER
. Register a new user face.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show program version.
.SH INTERNATIONALIZATION
The system supports multiple languages through environment variables:
.TP
English
.B LANG=en_US.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Français
.B LANG=fr_FR.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Español
.B LANG=es_ES.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Deutsch
.B LANG=de_DE.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Italiano
.B LANG=it_IT.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Português
.B LANG=pt_BR.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
Русский
.B LANG=ru_RU.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
日本語
.B LANG=ja_JP.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
中文
.B LANG=zh_CN.UTF-8 hello doctor
.TP
العربية
.B LANG=ar_AR.UTF-8 hello doctor
.SH EXEMPLES
.TP
Register a new user:
.B hello add john
.TP
Test authentication:
.B hello test john
.TP
List all users:
.B hello list
.TP
Run system diagnostics:
.B hello doctor
.TP
Select camera:
.B hello select-camera
.TP
Remove user:
.B hello remove john
.SH SERVICE DAEMON
The system runs a background daemon service accessible via:
.B systemctl status linux-hello
.PP
Start the daemon:
.B sudo systemctl start linux-hello
.PP
Enable on boot:
.B sudo systemctl enable linux-hello
.PP
View logs:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello -f
.SH INTÉGRATION PAM
To enable facial authentication for login, add to
.I /etc/pam.d/login
or
.I /etc/pam.d/sudo
:
.PP
.RS
auth    sufficient    pam_exec.so quiet stdout /usr/lib/linux-hello/pam_linux_hello.py
.RE
.PP
This will attempt facial authentication before falling back to password.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration files are stored in:
.B /etc/linux-hello/
.PP
User face data is stored in:
.B /var/lib/linux-hello/faces/
.PP
System logs are available via journalctl:
.B journalctl -u linux-hello
.SH VOIR AUSSI
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR journalctl (1),
.BR pam (8)
